oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Survey map of the Hindenburg Line in France
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: This map shows the Hindenburg Line in France. In the corner the map is identified as an ordnance survey from March 1918. It also states the allied trenches are identified in red and enemy trenches are in blue. This map was used by James M. Johnston during World War I. James Johnston served in HQ Co., Ord. Corps, attached to the 114th MG Battn., 30th Div.
